data.name: Button34.ToolTip
data.value: Will make a plain ".type" file text to specify the backup memory type on a per-game basis Useful on any ostic GBA game with "save backup message error" for Example: - Super Mario Advance 4 - Super Mario Bros. 3 - Use a 128 flash save type - Classic NES title - Use a blank eeprom save type

data.name: CheckBox16.ToolTip
data.value:
Use Joypad to navigate into gui
Layout joypad reflect XBox controller:
D-PAD directions = Keyboard Arrow direction A button = ENTER KEY X button = SHIFT KEY (on list rom), SPACE key on GUI Y button = F KEY (add to favourites) B button = CANCEL KEY L button = BACK TAB KEY, on list rom swap rear 10 entries R button = TAB KEY, on list rom swap next 10 entries SELECT = Swap from list rom to upper Gui menu START = Swap from list rom to Tabcontrol

data.name: CheckBox12.ToolTip
data.value: Add real time clock (rtc) option to ".type" file text to specify the backup memory type on a per-game basis Useful on any ostic GBA game with "save backup message error" for Example: - Pokemon - Versione Smeraldo (Italy)

data.name: Label48.Text
data.value: MedClient will send crypted information of your current NetPlay session on a external server. No sensible data are stored, (Nick, Server, Port, Title Game, Mednafen Module and Rom CRC). This file will be deleted form external server when you close Netplay session or when you close MedClient window.
